div.p:
In all avoid Irregular Extremes, and wilde Extravagancies; be for safe and sober Principles and Practices. It was a wise mans Motto, (viz. Sir Nicholas Bacon
                     •
                  ) Mediocria Firmâ: Things carried with Moderation and Mediocrity are firm and stable; Extremes soon run themselves out of breath, tumble down of themselves, and so end in Confusion.
